President Donald Trump and Vice President Mike Pence met with their Cabinet and senior members of their Administration to discuss ongoing Federal support for Hurricane Harvey response and recovery. President Trump emphasized his expectations that all departments and agencies stay fully engaged and positioned to support his priority of saving lives. He directed his Federal team to remain fully engaged and in support of the Governors of Texas and Louisiana. The President and Vice President also expressed their gratitude to volunteer and faith-based organizations helping those affected by the hurricane and extended their thoughts and prayers to those impacted.